                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4314: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Considering the debate recently held in Congress with relation to the use of
                    American troops in foreign countries, unless it is absolutely demanded by
                    conditions, the Department is reluctant to give authority for an increase in the
                    present contingent. Make a specific report as to the reasons for the requested
                    increase. State whether the lives and property of Americans are endangered or
                    are likely to be.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
